===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: A drawing of a turtle seen from the side and from above (Bronze inscriptions).

===Etymology 1===
{{der|zh|aav}}. Compare {{cog|mnw|ဂွိ||soft-shell turtle|tr=gwi}}, {{cog|cbn|ทะวี่ʔ||soft-shell turtle|tr=tha wìiʼ}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
;"(Cantonese) signature"
:Signatures are usually [[scribble]]d and difficult to recognize, making it resemble the character {{lang|zh|龜}}, which is with many strokes.
;"(Hong Kong Cantonese) police"
:In the past, Hong Kong police uniforms were in dark green, similar to colour of turtles.

